import {Fragment} from "react" import {useSelector} from "react-redux" import {useParams} from "react-router-dom" const UpdateEntry = () => { const params = useParams() const {id} = params const entry = useSelector(state => state.entries.find(data => data._id === id)) console.log(entry) return (

{entry.title}

{entry.topic}

{entry.entry}

 ) } export default UpdateEntry
